Old Fashioned Tea Cake Cookies
  --Monique Kilgore

1/4 c unsalted butter room temperature
1/4 c butter-flavored shortening
1 c sugar
1 egg room temperature
1 tsp lemon zest (optional)
1/2 vanilla bean scraped (or 1-2 tsp vanilla extract)
2 c ap flour
2 tsp baking powder
1/2 tsp salt
1/4 tsp groung nutmeg
1/4 c buttermilk

In a large bowl, cream together butter and shortening until creamy. Mix in sugar until well combined. Mix in the egg. Mix in lemon zest, if using, and vanilla bean paste. Set aside. In a medium bowl, sift together flour, baking powder, salt, and nutmeg. Mix the dry ingredients into the wet ingredients, alternating with the buttermilk. Turn the dough onto a smooth surface and knead until the dough is soft. Shape into a disk and cover with plastic wrap. Refrigerate for 1 hr (or freeze for 30 min) Preheat oven to 350F. Line a large baking sheet with parchment paper. Set aside. Remove dough from fridge and plastic wrap. Knead the dough to soften it. Roll the dough to 1/4" thick. (roll the dough between parchment to prevent sticking) Use a round cookie cutter to cut out circle shapes. Place cookies on the prepared pan ~2" apart. Bake for 8-10 min until bottoms are lightly golden. Let cookies int on the pan for 3 min before placing them on a cooling rack to finish cooling.
 Once cooled, store in an airtight container.
